summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling resolution 1645 (2005) and its paragraph 27,
Reaffirming the importance of UN peacebuilding work and need for sustained support and resources,
Recognizing the Peacebuilding Commission's role in addressing countries' needs emerging from conflict,

1. Welcomes the report "Review of the United Nations Peacebuilding Architecture" (S/2010/393);
2. Requests UN actors to implement report recommendations within their mandates;
3. Recognizes peacebuilding work requires sustained support and resources;
4. Requests the Peacebuilding Commission to report on progress in implementing recommendations;
5. Calls for a comprehensive review in 5 years following the procedure in resolution 1645 (2005);
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
